reviews.review_text: Recently visited Masak restaurant for dinner and had a delightful experience. We started with French Fries, Pepper Chicken, and Dragon Chicken as startersâ€”all were perfectly cooked and very tasty. For the main course, we tried the Biryani, which was a bit spicy but full of flavor, and the Chicken Fried Rice, which was excellent. To complement the meal, we had Lemon Soda, which was refreshing and delicious. The service was exceptionalâ€”waiters were well-trained, very quick, and attentive. Overall, a great place for a tasty and enjoyable dining experience!

The vibe is awesome. Loved the food, quantity is decent (rice was enough for 2 but I could've finished the starter alone). Pricing is good for the service they offer. I don't know why it was so empty the day I visited, but that just added more brownie points.

Was an exceptional experience to dine in. Am always concerned about how my parents would enjoy the food, this place was not worried at all.

We had a wonderful mix of starters - Chicken (not sure on the name), the staff helped us by recommending it and was happy as it was a mix of mild spice and a little more spice.

The Butter chicken and the naan took the cake. My dad actually ordered another plate just to take home and enjoy it... Absolute knock out.

We had a Veg thali which was filled with lovely Veg assorted and a chicken thali.

Food was good. Ambience was stellar. A mix of goan music and hindi music played. We met a Politician from dad's village too on the day we
visited which was a plus plus ðŸ™‚.

Don't hesitate to try this place out if you are in Panjim.

Thank you Masak team, keep up your stellar work.
